.Dd April 2, 2026
.Dt GALE 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm gale
.Nd isolated package management for developers
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Ar command
.Op Ar args ...
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
is a package manager for developer CLI tools that
replaces Homebrew, Nix, and home-manager.
It installs packages into versioned, isolated store
directories and manages environment activation through
atomic generation snapshots.
.Pp
Packages are declared in
.Pa gale.toml .
Prebuilt binaries from GHCR are preferred; source
builds are the automatic fallback.
Every package can be built from source \(em binaries
are a cache, not a requirement.
.Pp
.Nm
supports both global packages
.Pq installed to Pa ~/.gale
and per-project environments
.Pq via direnv integration .
.Sh COMMANDS
.Ss Package Management
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Cm install Ar pkg Ns Op @ Ns Ar ver
Install a package.
Downloads a prebuilt binary if available, otherwise
builds from source.
Use
.Ar pkg@ver
to install a specific version.
.Pp
.Dl $ gale install jq
.Dl $ gale install go@1.26.1
.It Cm remove Ar pkg
Remove a package from the store and
.Pa gale.toml .
.Pp
.Dl $ gale remove htop
.It Cm add Ar pkg Ns Op @ Ns Ar ver ...
Add one or more packages to
.Pa gale.toml
without installing.
Useful for declaring dependencies before running
.Cm sync .
.Pp
.Dl $ gale add ripgrep fd bat
.It Cm sync
Install all packages declared in
.Pa gale.toml
at their pinned versions.
Typically invoked automatically by direnv.
.Pp
.Dl $ gale sync
.It Cm update Op Ar pkg Ns Op @ Ns Ar ver ...
Update packages to the latest version, or to a specific
version with
.Ar pkg@ver .
Skips pinned packages unless explicitly named.
.Pp
Use
.Fl -no-install
to rewrite
.Pa gale.toml
pins without building; run
.Cm sync
afterward to install.
Use
.Fl -no-refresh
to skip the automatic tap refresh.
.Pp
.Dl $ gale update
.Dl $ gale update jq@1.8.1
.Dl $ gale update --no-install jq
.It Cm switch Ar pkg Ar version
Switch a package already declared in
.Pa gale.toml
to a specific version.
Bypasses
.Ic [pinned] ,
works for downgrades as well as upgrades, and refuses to
add packages that aren't already declared (use
.Cm install
for that).
Accepts both two-arg and
.Ar pkg@ver
forms.
.Pp
.Dl $ gale switch gh 2.89.0
.Dl $ gale switch gh@2.89.0
.It Cm list Op Fl -scope Ar all|shared|host Op Fl g | Fl p | Fl a
List packages declared in
.Pa gale.toml
with their versions.
Use
.Fl -scope
to filter shared and host overlay entries
.Pq default Li all .
Use
.Fl g
to list global packages from inside a project,
.Fl p
to force project scope, or
.Fl a
to list both with section headers.
.Pp
.Dl $ gale list
.Dl $ gale list --scope host
.Dl $ gale list -a
.It Cm gc
Remove unused package versions from the store and
old generations.
Keeps only versions referenced by
.Pa gale.toml
and the current generation.
.Pp
.Dl $ gale gc --dry-run
.Dl $ gale gc
.It Cm pin Ar pkg
Pin a package to its current version.
Pinned packages are skipped by
.Cm update
unless explicitly named.
.Pp
.Dl $ gale pin go
.It Cm unpin Ar pkg
Remove the pin on a package, allowing
.Cm update
to upgrade it again.
.Pp
.Dl $ gale unpin go
.El
.Ss Inspection
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Cm info Ar pkg Op Fl g | Fl p
Show package metadata: version, store path, scope,
config path, and pin status.
For uninstalled packages, shows registry information.
With
.Fl g ,
read only the global
.Pa gale.toml \(em
this is how to view a global entry that a project
.Pa gale.toml
shadows.
.Pp
.Dl $ gale info jq
.Dl $ gale info jq -g
.It Cm which Ar binary Op Fl g | Fl p
Show which installed package provides a binary and
print its full path.
Scope flags select which generation's
.Pa current/bin
is searched.
.Pp
.Dl $ gale which jq
.Dl jq@1.8.1
.Dl /Users/you/.gale/pkg/jq/1.8.1/bin/jq
.It Cm outdated Op Fl -recipes Op Fl -no-refresh Op Fl g | Fl p
Show packages that have newer versions available in
the registry.
Pass
.Fl -recipes
to resolve against a local recipes checkout instead, or
.Fl -no-refresh
to skip the automatic tap refresh.
.Pp
.Dl $ gale outdated
.Dl jq 1.7.1 -> 1.8.1
.It Cm inspect Op Ar pkg | Fl -all
Audit installed packages for linkage issues:
unresolvable
.Va @rpath
references, stale rpath entries, and mismatches between
binary references and the recipe's declared deps.
Exits non-zero when issues are found, so CI can gate on it.
Use
.Fl -all
to scan every installed package, or
.Fl -json
for machine-readable output.
.Pp
.Dl $ gale inspect jq
.Dl $ gale inspect --all --json
.It Cm doctor Op Fl -repair
Check the gale installation for common problems:
PATH configuration, store integrity, stale generations,
host-overlay shadows, and lib farm drift.
Use
.Fl -repair
to rebuild active generations and re-sign Mach-O binaries.
.Pp
.Dl $ gale doctor
.Dl $ gale doctor --repair
.It Cm search Ar query
Search for packages by name or description.
.Pp
.Dl $ gale search json
.El
.Ss Generation Management
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Cm generations Op Fl g | Fl p
List all generations, marking the active one.
Scope flags select the project or global generation
directory.
.Pp
.Dl $ gale generations
.Dl $ gale generations -g
.It Cm generations diff Op Ar from Op Ar to Op Fl g | Fl p
Show packages added and removed between two
generations.
Defaults to comparing the current generation with
the previous one.
.Pp
.Dl $ gale generations diff
.Dl $ gale generations diff 3 5
.It Cm generations rollback Op Ar N Op Fl g | Fl p
Switch to a previous generation.
Defaults to the previous generation (current \- 1).
Atomic symlink swap, same as install/sync.
.Pp
.Dl $ gale generations rollback
.Dl $ gale generations rollback 3
.El
.Ss Project Environment
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Cm init
Create a
.Pa gale.toml
and
.Pa .envrc
in the current directory, setting up direnv integration.
.Pp
.Dl $ gale init
.It Cm env Op Fl -vars-only Op Fl g | Fl p
Print shell export commands to activate the environment.
Use
.Fl -vars-only
to print only
.Ic [vars]
exports from
.Pa gale.toml .
Use
.Fl g
to opt into global vars and PATH from inside a project.
.Pp
.Dl $ eval "$(gale env)"
.Dl $ eval "$(gale env -g)"
.It Cm shell
Open an interactive shell with the project environment
activated.
.Pp
.Dl $ gale shell
.It Cm run Ar cmd Op Ar args ...
Run a command in the project environment.
Syncs packages if
.Pa gale.toml
has changed.
.Pp
.Dl $ gale run go test ./...
.It Cm hook direnv
Print the
.Fn use_gale
shell function for
.Pa ~/.config/direnv/direnvrc .
.Pp
.Dl $ gale hook direnv >> ~/.config/direnv/direnvrc
.El
.Ss Recipe Development
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Cm build Ar recipe.toml Op Fl -debug
Build a package from a local recipe file.
Produces a
.Pa .tar.zst
archive.
Use
.Fl -debug
for unoptimized builds with debug symbols.
.Pp
.Dl $ gale build recipes/j/jq.toml
.It Cm lint Ar recipe.toml ...
Validate one or more recipe files for errors and
warnings.
.Pp
.Dl $ gale lint recipes/j/jq.toml
.It Cm create-recipe Ar repo Op Fl o Ar dir
Generate a recipe from a GitHub repository using AI.
Accepts
.Ar owner/repo ,
.Ar github.com/owner/repo ,
or a full URL.
.Pp
Automatically detects build systems, computes source
SHA256, and validates with lint.
Missing dependencies are created recursively (up to
6 levels deep).
.Pp
When run inside a gale-recipes directory, writes
recipes to
.Pa recipes/<letter>/<name>.toml .
Otherwise prints to stdout.
Use
.Fl o
to specify an output directory.
.Pp
Requires an Anthropic API key in
.Pa ~/.gale/config.toml .
.Pp
.Dl $ gale create-recipe jqlang/jq
.Dl $ gale create-recipe -o recipes/ benhoyt/inih
.El
.Ss Supply Chain Security
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Cm audit Ar pkg Op Fl g | Fl p
Rebuild a package from source and compare its SHA256
against the installed binary.
A match confirms the build is reproducible; most builds
are not yet deterministic, so a mismatch does not
indicate tampering.
Scope flags select which lockfile to read the
installed hash from.
.Pp
.Dl $ gale audit jq
.It Cm verify Ar pkg Op Fl g | Fl p
Check the Sigstore attestation for an installed
package's prebuilt binary.
Scope flags select which lockfile to read the
installed version from.
.Pp
.Dl $ gale verify jq
.It Cm sbom Op Ar pkg Op Fl -json Op Fl g | Fl p | Fl a
Show a software bill of materials for installed
packages.
Use
.Fl -json
for machine-readable output.
With
.Fl a ,
emit entries from both the project and global
gale.toml; each entry gets a
.Ic scope
field
.Pq Sq project No or Sq global .
.Pp
.Dl $ gale sbom
.Dl $ gale sbom jq --json
.Dl $ gale sbom -a
.El
.Ss Repository Management
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Cm repo add Ar name Ar url
Add a recipe repository with the given name and URL.
.It Cm repo remove Ar name
Remove a recipe repository.
.It Cm repo list
List configured recipe repositories.
.It Cm repo init Ar name
Create a new recipe repository scaffold.
.It Cm repo update Op Ar name
Update one or all recipe repositories.
.El
.Ss Shell Completion
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Cm completion bash | zsh | fish | powershell
Generate a shell completion script.
.Pp
.Dl $ gale completion zsh > ~/.zfunc/_gale
.El
.Sh FLAGS
.Ss Global Flags
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Fl v , -verbose
Verbose output.
.It Fl n , -dry-run
Show what would happen without making changes.
Applies to all mutating commands:
.Cm install , remove , sync , update , gc .
.It Fl q , -quiet
Suppress non-essential status output.
Warnings and errors still print.
.It Fl -plain
Disable color, progress bars, and step indicators.
Use when capturing output for logs or tests.
.It Fl -no-color
Disable colored output.
Same as setting
.Ev NO_COLOR
to a non-empty value.
.It Fl -error-format Ar text|json
Format top-level runtime errors.
Default
.Li text .
.El
.Ss Scope Flags
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Fl g , -global
Target the global
.Pa ~/.gale/gale.toml .
.It Fl p , -project
Target the project
.Pa gale.toml .
.Pp
When neither flag is set, defaults to project scope
if a
.Pa gale.toml
exists in the directory tree, otherwise global.
Applies to mutation commands
.Pq Cm install , add , remove , sync , update , switch
and to read-only commands
.Pq Cm list , info , sbom , outdated , env , which , verify , audit , generations .
.It Fl a , -all
For inventory commands
.Pq Cm list , sbom ,
list packages from both project and global
.Pa gale.toml
under
.Sq Project:
and
.Sq Global:
section headers.
Mutually exclusive with
.Fl g
and
.Fl p .
.El
.Ss Source Strategy Flags
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Fl -path Ar dir
Build from a local source directory.
Version is derived from git describe.
.It Fl -build
Build from source, skipping prebuilt binaries.
.It Fl -git
Clone the source repository and build from HEAD.
.It Fl -recipe Ar file
Use a specific local recipe file.
.It Fl -recipes Op Ar path
Resolve recipes from a local directory instead of
the registry.
Defaults to sibling
.Pa ../gale-recipes/
when used without argument.
.El
.Ss Build Flags
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Fl -debug
Build with debug flags:
.Fl O0 Fl g ,
no symbol stripping.
.It Fl -release
Build with release flags, overriding any debug setting
in the recipe or config.
.El
.Ss Output Flags
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Fl -json
Output in JSON format
.Pq Cm sbom .
.It Fl -vars-only
Print only
.Ic [vars]
exports
.Pq Cm env .
.El
.Sh BUILD ENVIRONMENT
Build steps run in a clean shell with only essential
tools on PATH.
The following variables are set:
.Pp
.Bl -tag -width "DYLD_FALLBACK_LIBRARY_PATH" -compact
.It Ev PREFIX
Install destination directory.
.It Ev VERSION
Package version from the recipe.
.It Ev JOBS
CPU count for parallel builds.
.It Ev OS
Operating system
.Pq Li darwin , Li linux .
.It Ev ARCH
Architecture
.Pq Li arm64 , Li amd64 .
.It Ev PLATFORM
.Ev OS Ns - Ns Ev ARCH
.Pq e.g. Li darwin-arm64 .
.El
.Pp
When build dependencies are installed, additional
paths are set:
.Pp
.Bl -tag -width "DYLD_FALLBACK_LIBRARY_PATH" -compact
.It Ev LIBRARY_PATH
Library directories from dependencies.
.It Ev C_INCLUDE_PATH
Header directories from dependencies.
.It Ev PKG_CONFIG_PATH
Pkg-config directories from dependencies.
.It Ev CMAKE_LIBRARY_PATH
CMake library search path.
.It Ev CMAKE_INCLUDE_PATH
CMake include search path.
.It Ev CMAKE_PREFIX_PATH
CMake prefix path (cmake builds only, semicolon-separated).
.It Ev LD_LIBRARY_PATH
Dynamic linker path (Linux only).
.It Ev DYLD_FALLBACK_LIBRARY_PATH
Dynamic linker fallback path (macOS only).
.El
.Pp
Compiler flags default to
.Fl O2
for release builds and
.Fl O0 Fl g
for debug builds.
User-set
.Ev CFLAGS ,
.Ev CXXFLAGS ,
and
.Ev LDFLAGS
are never overridden.
.Sh EXAMPLES
Install packages and set up a project:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
$ gale install ripgrep bat fd
$ cd myproject
$ gale init
$ gale add go@1.26.1 golangci-lint
$ gale sync
.Ed
.Pp
Update everything except pinned packages:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
$ gale pin go
$ gale update
$ gale unpin go
.Ed
.Pp
Use direnv for automatic project environments:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
$ gale hook direnv >> ~/.config/direnv/direnvrc
$ cd myproject
$ gale init
$ direnv allow
.Ed
.Pp
Build and test a recipe:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
$ gale create-recipe jqlang/jq
$ gale build recipes/j/jq.toml
$ gale install jq --recipe recipes/j/jq.toml
.Ed
.Pp
Audit supply chain integrity:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
$ gale audit jq
$ gale verify jq
$ gale sbom --json
.Ed
.Sh CONFIGURATION
Application settings in
.Pa ~/.gale/config.toml :
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Ic [build]
.Bl -tag -width "debug" -compact
.It Va debug
When true, all builds use debug flags.
Default: false.
.El
.It Ic [anthropic]
.Bl -tag -width "prompt_file" -compact
.It Va api_key
Anthropic API key for
.Cm create-recipe .
.It Va prompt_file
Path to a file appended to the recipe creation
system prompt.
.El
.It Ic [registry]
.Bl -tag -width "url" -compact
.It Va url
Override the recipe registry URL.
.El
.El
.Pp
Package declarations in
.Pa gale.toml :
.Bd -literal -offset indent
[packages]
jq = "1.8.1"
go = "1.26.1"

[pinned]
go = true

[vars]
GOPATH = "${HOME}/go"

[hosts.my-mac.packages]
fzf = "0.50"

[hosts.my-server.packages]
htop = "3.0"
.Ed
.Pp
Top-level
.Ic [packages]
applies on every machine.
.Ic [hosts. Ns Ar name Ns Ic .packages]
sections add machine-specific packages when the local
hostname matches
.Ar name .
Host entries override shared entries when both
declare the same package.
.Ic [hosts. Ns Ar name Ns Ic .pinned]
mirrors the shared
.Ic [pinned]
behavior per host.
The active host is
.Ev GALE_HOST
if set, otherwise the value returned by
.Xr hostname 1 .
.Pp
Use
.Fl -host Ar name
on
.Cm add , remove , pin ,
and
.Cm unpin
to target a host section.
.Fl -host current
expands to the current machine.
.Sh ENVIRONMENT
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Ev NO_COLOR
Disables colored output when set to a non-empty value,
regardless of TTY status.
Follows the
.Lk https://no-color.org
convention.
An empty value is ignored.
.It Ev GALE_HOST
Overrides the hostname used to select
.Ic [hosts. Ns Ar X Ns Ic ]
sections in
.Pa gale.toml .
Defaults to
.Xr hostname 1 .
.El
.Sh FILES
.Bl -tag -width "~/.gale/config.toml" -compact
.It Pa ~/.gale/gale.toml
Global package declarations.
.It Pa ~/.gale/config.toml
Application settings (API keys, registry URL).
.It Pa ~/.gale/pkg/
Package store.
One directory per package per version.
.It Pa ~/.gale/current/
Symlink to the active generation directory.
Add
.Pa ~/.gale/current/bin
to PATH.
.It Pa gale.toml
Project package declarations.
.It Pa gale.lock
Lockfile with SHA256 hashes for reproducibility.
.El
.Sh EXIT STATUS
.Ex -std
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr brew 1 ,
.Xr direnv 1
